1 7–1501.
2 (a) In this subtitle the following words have the meanings indicated.
3 (f) “Fund” means the Safe Schools Fund.
4 7–1508.
5 (g) (1) For fiscal year 2020 and each fiscal year thereafter, the Governor shall
6 include in the annual budget bill an appropriation of $10,000,000 to the Fund for the
7 purpose of providing grants to local school systems and local law enforcement agencies to
8 assist in meeting the requirements of subsection (e) of this section.
9 (2) Grants provided under this subsection [shall]:
10 (I) SHALL be made to each local school system based on the number
11 of schools in each school system in proportion to the total number of public schools in the
12 State in the prior year; AND
13 (II) MAY BE REALLOCATED TO LOCAL SCHOOL SYSTEMS THAT
14 HAVE FULLY EXPENDED THEIR ALLOCATION AND DEMONSTRATE NEED WITHIN THE
15 SAME FISCAL YEAR.
16 (3) TWICE ANNUALLY, THE SUBCABINET SHALL NOTIFY EACH LOCAL
17 SCHOOL SYSTEM REGARDING THE STATUS OF THE ALLOCATIONS MADE UNDER
18 PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION.
19 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
20 1, 2025.
